\section intro_sec Introduction

Plus (Public software Library for UltraSound) is an open-source software package for tracked ultrasound image acquisition, calibration, and processing. Plus applications include complete end-user software applications for spatial and temporal calibration (fCal) and real-time data acquisition, processing and streaming (PlusServer). For building complete image-guided therapy applications you can use the 3D Slicer and the <a href="http://www.slicerigt.org">SlicerIGT extension</a>.

Overview papers and presentations:
- <a href="http://perk.cs.queensu.ca/sites/perk.cs.queensu.ca/files/biblio/Lasso2014a.pdf">Paper published in IEEE-TBME</a>
- <a href="https://subversion.assembla.com/svn/plus/trunk/doc/overview/PlusOverview.pptx">Technology overview presentation</a>
- <a href="https://subversion.assembla.com/svn/plus/trunk/doc/overview/SlicerIgtPlusIntro-NCIGT2013.pptx">Overview presentation with some clinical applications</a>
- <a href="https://subversion.assembla.com/svn/plus/trunk/doc/overview/PlusArchitectureOverview.pptx">Multi-channel architecture overview presentation</a>

